All in order.

240
00:24:25,190 --> 00:24:34,150
Now it remains only to pick the outer diameter for the sphere and toroid.

241
00:24:36,490 --> 00:24:39,430
Say 250 mm.

242
00:24:41,290 --> 00:24:43,390
240 mm.

243
00:24:46,150 --> 00:24:48,570
220 mm.

244
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:55,740
Approximately 225 mm will be the sphere.

245
00:24:55,740 --> 00:24:57,140
Well, and so on.

246
00:24:58,800 --> 00:25:06,040
Now when we did the calculations, we can stop on optimal builds.

247
00:25:06,620 --> 00:25:16,820
Once more reminder: the most optimal coil build is the one that'll have the smallest isolated capacity.

248
00:25:17,300 --> 00:25:22,540
But this is all depending on what goals you pursue.

249
00:25:22,540 --> 00:25:32,780
If you're doing a Tesla transformer for a generator, then you specifically need the isolated capacity to be smaller here.

250
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:37,500
Less consumption of the coil until it reaches its operating mode.

251
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:53,720
And if you do a Tesla coil specifically for light-noise effects, for beautiful streamers, then you'll specifically be interested in an isolated capacity with bigger geometric sizes here.

252
00:25:54,100 --> 00:25:58,940
Then it'll charge to a bigger potential and the breakdown will be longer.

253
00:25:59,060 --> 00:26:05,480
You also shouldn't leave the hot end of a Tesla transformer completely without an isolated capacity.

254
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:09,640
Here you need to feel the coil, if I can say so.

255
00:26:10,460 --> 00:26:21,260
Look at the winding geometry itself, and if you put a small ball there — say you have a 110 pipe and some ball of 30 mm — then this will also be not optimal.

256
00:26:21,760 --> 00:26:25,140
That is, everything has its optimal ratios.

257
00:26:26,280 --> 00:26:34,480
You can't perch a big toroid on a small winding height, and you also can't put a small ball on a big winding.

258
00:26:35,520 --> 00:26:37,540
Strive to optimize the system.

259
00:26:37,540 --> 00:26:53,340
Because this isolated capacity, it ultimately will be the radiating part of the Tesla transformer for the wave processes we'll need for creating a generator.

260
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:58,820
In general, we finished with online calculators.

261
00:26:58,940 --> 00:27:03,840
Now let's move to the important moment of how to calculate inductor length.

262
00:27:03,840 --> 00:27:05,200
So, item number 2.

263
00:27:06,340 --> 00:27:20,960
The Tesla transformer is a discrete system for us, and its discreteness consists in the fact that we can calculate the inductor length by ratio to the wire length of the Tesla transformer.

264
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:24,200
This can be done in two ways.

265
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:36,440
Say, we take a certain inductor length in meters, multiply by some whole number, and get the total length of the Tesla transformer.

266
00:27:36,800 --> 00:27:50,220
But this way is slightly inconvenient in terms of needing to calculate the Tesla transformer itself, so it comes out good for us by our frequency, proceeding from this.

267
00:27:51,040 --> 00:27:53,700
Then we act in the second way.

268
00:27:53,700 --> 00:28:09,780
We, knowing the length of one turn wound on the Tesla transformer frame, can multiply this turn length by a whole number, and this way we get the total length of the Tesla transformer inductor.

269
00:28:10,180 --> 00:28:15,300
Now I'll show an example of calculation for the inductor under the 110 pipe.

270
00:28:15,300 --> 00:28:31,120
The question of choosing inductor, diameter, winding — it's strictly individual for each Tesla transformer and depends on what you work on, on the final goal you want to achieve.

271
00:28:31,700 --> 00:28:44,660
I asked these questions to many people, some couldn't at all clearly answer me, and the most identically and rationally to these questions two people answered.

272
00:28:44,660 --> 00:28:51,900
This is Alexander Vladimirovich Romanov and a person under the nickname on the internet Ruslan X.

273
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:57,280
Both people have big practice in Tesla building.

274
00:28:58,920 --> 00:29:16,840
And if to summarize the moments people talk about, those who work more on spark gaps incline to the opinion that a Tesla transformer should be classical, as Tesla bequeathed to make.

275
00:29:16,980 --> 00:29:35,760
This is only 1-2 turns of primary winding, thick copper tube, or busbar, whose length is picked proceeding from the turn length of the Tesla transformer.

276
00:29:35,760 --> 00:29:46,100
For example, multiply turn length by 2 and get the total length of one inductor turn for this transformer.

277
00:29:46,100 --> 00:30:10,020
And there are such strictly personal observations from some, that there's even some resonance by copper mass — between the copper mass in the inductor tube and the copper mass of the Tesla transformer turns — that affects it.

278
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:15,920
I didn't check this moment, I can't say anything personally on this matter.

279
00:30:16,560 --> 00:30:36,300
The most accurately noted moment is also that the surface area of this copper tube or busbar should correspond to the surface area of the conductors of the Tesla transformer's secondary winding that this inductor affects.

280
00:30:36,300 --> 00:30:41,120
Here we have the next moment that we need to stop on.

281
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:55,540
We need to understand that the classical transformer in a Tesla transformer build is only the part of its winding located in the zone affected by the inductor.

282
00:30:56,340 --> 00:31:00,360
All the rest of the part is exclusively a waveguide.

283
00:31:01,260 --> 00:31:15,580
But we now do the calculation of the inductor length for a build that'll work on semiconductor inverters, bridge or half-bridge scheme.

284
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:34,580
And if we'll be guided by Tesla's rules and other people who work proceeding from the fact that for a spark gap inductor optimal 1-2 turns, then this'll be too big a load on our semiconductor transistors.

285
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:41,800
So we should take a bigger amount of wire by length.

286
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:52,740
Say, for a 110 frame I'd personally do an inductor winding on a 153 frame in the form of a cylinder.

287
00:31:52,740 --> 00:32:02,860
Here the optimal gap is about 2 cm between Tesla transformer wire and inductor wire.

288
00:32:03,280 --> 00:32:20,160
This gap is chosen not only proceeding from the absence of breakdown to the inductor, but also proceeding from the desired coupling coefficient between the inductor and the turns of the Tesla transformer it affects.

289
00:32:20,160 --> 00:32:23,780
Now we move directly to the calculation.

290
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:39,880
Earlier we calculated that for a frame diameter of 110 mm, the conductor length to be wound on this frame is 345 mm, or 34.5 cm.

291
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:47,680
So now we need to choose a whole number on which we multiply this length.

292
00:32:47,760 --> 00:32:50,340
In this case I stopped on 12.

293
00:32:51,500 --> 00:33:06,580
Based on what considerations I took it: since approximately I'd wind for a 110 pipe an inductor on a 153 mm frame, I also approximately calculated for it that the length of one revolution is 48 cm.

294
00:33:06,580 --> 00:33:15,820
For quality work of bridge and half-bridge schemes the turn count lies in the range of 5-8 pieces.

295
00:33:17,300 --> 00:33:23,520
This is approximately 8 turns by my counts, multiply by 50, this is 4 meters.

296
00:33:24,460 --> 00:33:34,460
And in this case I multiplied the Tesla transformer's turn length by 12 and got a total inductor length of 4 m 14 cm.

297
00:33:35,420 --> 00:33:47,440
Once more I repeat, this inductor length will be unchanged for this Tesla transformer regardless of the geometry of the inductor winding.

298
00:33:47,600 --> 00:33:57,340
That is you can lay it flat, cylindrical, or in the form of a cone — this won't affect the final length.

299
00:33:57,340 --> 00:34:08,300
Now schematically I drew the bridge or half-bridge scheme if we replace these keys with capacitors with a middle point.

300
00:34:09,100 --> 00:34:21,460
So, our calculated length of 4.14 m is the length from this point to this point, effectively the transistor leads.

301
00:34:21,460 --> 00:34:31,040
In this length enter the free leads from the inductor going to the bridge block.

302
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:35,840
And also the leads that are from the capacitors.

303
00:34:36,180 --> 00:34:40,640
All this enters this length of 4 m 14 cm.

304
00:34:42,060 --> 00:34:47,020
Here, this end of the inductor will be the upper end.

305
00:34:47,020 --> 00:35:02,840
That is by "upper" I mean if we wind around the Tesla transformer this inductor, it's the end directed toward the hot end of the Tesla transformer.

306
00:35:03,320 --> 00:35:09,580
The lower end accordingly will be the one directed toward the cold end of the Tesla transformer.

307
00:35:10,580 --> 00:35:22,640
And the capacity that'll determine for us resonance jointly with the inductor — it's placed at the upper end of the inductor.

308
00:35:23,240 --> 00:35:30,900
If the scheme is half-bridge, then the lower end of the inductor goes to the middle point between the capacitors.

309
00:35:30,900 --> 00:35:33,480
So, we understood the first rule.

310
00:35:34,720 --> 00:35:42,180
The Tesla transformer inductor correlates with the secondary winding's turn length.

311
00:35:43,460 --> 00:35:45,340
Now the second basic rule.

312
00:35:45,940 --> 00:35:50,760
How to choose conductor cross-section for winding the inductor.

313
00:35:50,760 --> 00:35:57,180
Ultimately this question reduces to the concept of the rule of areas.

314
00:35:58,000 --> 00:36:14,980
It turns out that we take the surface area of the inductor wire so it'd be approximately equal to the surface area of the turns of the Tesla transformer secondary winding that this inductor affects.

315
00:36:16,060 --> 00:36:29,980
That is, if we make a gap between turns in the inductor — say wind it cylindrically — then the bigger the gap, the bigger the cross-section our inductor should have.

316
00:36:30,780 --> 00:36:42,100
And conversely, if we lay the inductor turns close to each other, then the inductor cross-section can be smaller by its surface.

317
00:36:43,100 --> 00:37:00,040
If you choose wire that'll be of bigger cross-section by surface area, nothing bad will happen, you can only come to a material overspending.

318
00:37:00,720 --> 00:37:07,360
Well, and if the opposite case happens, the wire will be of smaller cross-section, the system will work worse.

319
00:37:08,800 --> 00:37:14,700
Now let me say several more words about our initial calculations.

320
00:37:15,560 --> 00:37:23,540
These preliminary calculations are connected with the moment for us to ultimately determine which build we'll do.

321
00:37:25,180 --> 00:37:31,520
Corrections to this calculation are made by fact when we wind the Tesla transformer.

322
00:37:31,520 --> 00:37:38,380
Mandatorily measure the clear turn count we laid.

323
00:37:38,920 --> 00:37:44,800
And check in several places of the Tesla transformer frame the turn length.

324
00:37:45,360 --> 00:37:51,680
For this wrap with tension one turn, make wires, and measure it by fact.

325
00:37:52,140 --> 00:37:56,260
And from this make our further corrections in calculation.

326
00:37:57,620 --> 00:38:11,620
I advise winding the conductor with some reserve, on the order of 2-3 m per frame, so we could then clearly tune our frequency.

327
00:38:12,040 --> 00:38:16,820
Because unwinding we can always do, and adding will be problematic.

328
00:38:17,220 --> 00:38:22,980
But this on the condition if we have some certain frequency we strive for.

329
00:38:22,980 --> 00:38:31,140
For example, we already made one transmitting coil, and we should accurately make the receiving one under it.

330
00:38:32,060 --> 00:38:45,380
Whoever is interested can also look at Denis Permakov's channel for the answers to my 8 questions that I asked Alexander Vladimirovich Romanov about the Tesla transformer inductor.

331
00:38:45,540 --> 00:38:52,200
This is the video under number 512, called "Questions on Tesla building."

332
00:38:53,200 --> 00:39:01,940
To all online calculators and channels presented in the overview in this video I'll give links in the description.

333
00:39:03,560 --> 00:39:08,460
On this, all the best to everyone, good mood, successful experiments.
